HEADWORD: Infelt
<hw>In"felt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets>
in + <ets>felt</ets>.]</ety> <def>Felt inwardly; heartfelt.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The baron stood afar off, or knelt in submissive, acknowledged,
<qex>infelt</qex> inferiority.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infeodation</ent>⟦br⟧
